        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            The inventory management system keeps track of item listings, storing the following data: <br>
            <ul>
                <li>Name</li>
                <li>Description</li>
                <li>Category</li>
                <li>Manufacturer</li>
                <li>Quantity</li>
            </ul><br>
            Key operations offered by the system:
            <ol>
                <li>Create listing - Users can <a href="/create_listing">Create new listings.</a></li>
                <li>Search listings - Any user can <a href="/search">Search through listings,</a></li>
                <li>Update listing - Users can update listings, after having searched for it.</li>
                <li>Remove listing - Users can remove listings, after having searched for it.</li>
                <li>Add and remove stock from listing - Users can add or take from the recorded amount of an item, after having searched for it.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
